TY  - JOUR
T1  - Murray and Reshef Revisited: Toward a Typology/Theory of Paradigms of National Trade Union Movements
AU  - Ofori-Dankwa, Joseph
Y1  - 1993/04/01
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1993.3997516
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1993.3997516
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 269
EP  - 292
VL  - 18
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This article builds on Murray and Reshef (1988) to develop a four-cell paradigm typology. Next, a theoretical model is developed to examine the determinants of national union paradigms, to present national case studies of the four paradigms, and to investigate the effects of paradigms on union organizational structures, levels of industrial conflict, and decline rates of national union movements. Finally, the effects that declining unionism has on paradigms and the research implications of this study are examined.
AB  - This article builds on Murray and Reshef (1988) to develop a four-cell paradigm typology. Next, a theoretical model is developed to examine the determinants of national union paradigms, to present national case studies of the four paradigms, and to investigate the effects of paradigms on union organizational structures, levels of industrial conflict, and decline rates of national union movements. Finally, the effects that declining unionism has on paradigms and the research implications of this study are examined.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1993.3997516
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.1993.3997516
Y2  - 2026/04/24
